videos.description: Gavin Holmes reverses the direction of his motion at the snap to catch a swing pass and beat the Texas Tech defense to the pylon to tie the game 7-7.
videos.headline: Misdirection motion frees Holmes for Baylor TD

videos.description: Tre King takes the goal line hand-off and powers it in to give the Red Raiders a 14-7 lead over the Bears.
videos.headline: Texas Tech's King lowers his shoulder through the goal line

videos.description: Quarterback Charlie Brewer fumbles while keeping the ball on a read-option and Texas Tech recovers.
videos.headline: Baylor's Brewer fumbles in red zone

videos.description: Nic Shimonek rolls out to his right and fires a pass to the front pylon where T.J. Vasher makes the touchdown catch to give the Red Raiders a 21-7 lead over the Bears.
videos.headline: Vasher extends lead for Texas Tech

videos.description: On fourth-and-goal, Texas Tech's defensive front stuffs Baylor's JaMycal Hasty to keep its 21-7 lead.
videos.headline: Red Raiders refuse entry into end zone

videos.description: Baylor's in field goal position, but Charlie Brewer rolls to his left and throws an interception in the end zone.
videos.headline: Baylor loses FG opportunity with interception

videos.description: Texas Tech's Tre King tries to extend the ball beyond the goal-line but is hit by Baylor's Jordan Williams who forces the fumble.
videos.headline: Baylor forces fumble with goal-line collision

videos.description: Charlie Brewer buys time outside the pocket and throws a dart to Pooh Stricklin for the 6-yard score.
videos.headline: Brewer scrambles and fires to Stricklin for Baylor TD

videos.description: Baylor appears to recover their onside kick attempt, but it's wiped out because the Red Raiders player called for a fair catch.
videos.headline: Fair catch negates Baylor's onside kick recovery

videos.description: Texas Tech's Cameron Batson catches the pass and spins on the sideline to avoid a Baylor tackler for a 30-yard score to go up 31-14.
videos.headline: Batson spins free for 30-yard TD

videos.description: Texas Tech's Douglas Coleman III strips Baylor's Tony Nicholson and runs 31 yards for the score to put the Red Raiders up 38-17 in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Texas Tech strips and scores to put Baylor away

videos.description: Denzel Mims catches the pass from Charlie Brewer for the 3-yard score. Mims finished the game with 12 catches for 152 yards.
videos.headline: Baylor's Mims scores on monster day
